{"word":"ἐπηρεφής","slug":"ἐπηρεφής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπηρεφής</b></el> <el>(ἐπ-ηρεφής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐρέφω'><el>ἐρέφω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>overhanging, beetling</i>, of cliffs, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>covered, sheltered</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}